main event: Multiple reports of unidentified flying objects observed in California during October 1965.
interesting points: One object was described as appearing like a twinkling star moving rapidly to the NNE at an altitude of 40-45 degrees., Another sighting involved a bright metallic object observed from the Space Systems Division building at Los Angeles., The sightings coincided with many other UFO reports during that period., The object observed from Los Angeles was seen for approximately 60 seconds before disappearing., Conclusions from the reports indicated that some objects were likely satellites.
sighted object: unidentified flying objects, one appearing as a twinkling star and another metallic object
witness description: Observers included staff at the Space Systems Division and an unnamed individual.
